#### REPL
type Foo = {x: int};
let f = fun x -> x.x + 1;
####

#### INPUT
print f {x="Hello"};
####
TypeError: Value is required to have type int by the + operator expression here:
type Foo = {x: int};
let f = fun x -> x.x + 1;
                 ^~~      
However, that value may have type str here:
print f {x="Hello"};
           ^~~~~~~   
Hint: To narrow down the cause of the type mismatch, consider adding an explicit type annotation here:
type Foo = {x: int};
let f = fun x: _ -> x.x + 1;
             +++
#### INPUT
print f Foo {x=42};
####
43
